{"questionId":"27820","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Celeste heated a cup of coffee and then let it cool to room temperature. Celeste found the&nbsp;coffee’s temperature, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi></math>, measured in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>°</mo><mtext>C</mtext></math>, could be modelled by the following function,</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mfenced><mi>t</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>71</mn><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0514</mn><mi>t</mi></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>23</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>0</mn></math>,</p>\n<p>where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> is the time, in minutes, after the coffee started to cool.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi></math> has a horizontal asymptote.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Given that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>T</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>(</mo><mn>50</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi></math>, find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>50</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>71</mn><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0514</mn><mfenced><mi>k</mi></mfenced></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>23</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>18</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>5000</mn></mrow><mn>257</mn></mfrac><mi>ln</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mn>27</mn><mn>71</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>18</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8101</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>M1</strong> </em>for a sketch showing a point of intersection between the exponential function and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>50</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27820","referenceCode":"22N.1.SL.TZ0.5d","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Given that T-1(50)=k, find the value of k.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.2—Functions, notation domain, range and inverse as reflection"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}